.TH GDLEX-OCR 1 "19 June 2026" "GD LEX OCR 0.4.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gdlex-ocr \- convert PDF documents to Markdown using local OCR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gdlex-ocr
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gdlex-ocr
starts the GD LEX OCR desktop application.
The application processes PDF documents locally with Docling and can
optionally create searchable PDFs using OCRmyPDF and Tesseract.
An explicitly configured local external command may also be used without
shell execution. Proprietary GUI applications are not automated.
.PP
The Sentenze / Impugnazioni module can create a local heuristic judgment card
from Markdown or after PDF conversion. It does not upload documents, does not
calculate final appeal deadlines, and does not replace professional review.
.PP
The Fascicoli PDP/TIAP module can analyze a local casefile folder without OCR.
It works on filenames, SHA-256 hashes, and lightweight TXT/CSV/HTML/XML
indexes. It does not read PDF contents, does not interpret the casefile
legally, and writes privacy-safe JSON and Markdown outputs without absolute
paths.
.PP
Python dependencies are not bundled in the Debian package.
At first launch the wrapper creates the per-user virtual environment
.IR ~/.local/share/gdlex-ocr/venv ,
upgrades pip, and installs the pinned dependencies from
.IR /usr/share/doc/gdlex-ocr/requirements.txt .
If essential imports are missing later, the wrapper updates the environment
before starting the application.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-setup\-venv
Force creation or update of the per-user virtual environment, then exit.
.TP
.B \-\-doctor
Print runtime diagnostics without starting the graphical application.
Exit status is 0 when all checks pass, 1 when essential runtime components
are missing, and 2 when only optional OCR tools or the Italian Tesseract
language are missing.
.TP
.BI \-\-ocr\-timeout " SECONDS"
Set the maximum OCRmyPDF timeout. The default is 1800 seconds.
.TP
.BI \-\-ocr\-jobs " N"
Pass the number of parallel jobs to OCRmyPDF. When omitted, OCRmyPDF keeps
its default behavior.
.TP
.BI \-\-analyze\-judgment " INPUT.md"
Analyze an already generated Markdown judgment locally. Requires
.B \-\-output
to point to the Markdown analysis file to write. This mode does not run OCR,
does not invoke Docling, and does not modify the input file.
.TP
.B \-\-prepend
With
.B \-\-analyze\-judgment ,
write the judgment card before the source Markdown in the output file.
.TP
.B \-\-analyze\-judgment\-after\-conversion
After PDF-to-Markdown conversion, write
.I sentenza_analysis.md
next to the main Markdown without modifying the main Markdown file. The runtime
manifest records a privacy-safe
.I judgment_analysis
section when available.
.TP
.BI \-\-analyze\-casefile " INPUT_DIR"
Analyze a local casefile folder. Requires
.B \-\-output
to point to the output directory. This mode scans files locally, computes
SHA-256 hashes, warns about possible duplicates, classifies documents from
filenames, detects and lightly parses TXT/CSV/HTML/XML indexes, and attempts
index-document matching. It does not run OCR, does not invoke Docling, does
not read PDF contents, and does not replace legal review.
.PP
The graphical application exposes equivalent OCRmyPDF timeout and jobs
controls in the OCR backend settings and a dedicated
.B "Analisi sentenza per impugnazione"
checkbox. OCRmyPDF output is streamed to the GUI log and run.log while
preserving timeout and error handling.
.PP
The GUI also provides a
.B Fascicolo
section for casefile folder analysis, with folder selection, output folder
selection and an
.B "Analizza fascicolo"
button. The analysis runs in a background thread, does not perform OCR, does
not read PDF contents, and generates
.IR fascicolo_index.json ,
.IR fascicolo_index.md ,
.I fascicolo_index.csv
and
.IR fascicolo_unita.csv .
The casefile folder path is not saved in settings. After completion,
.B "Apri cartella output"
and
.B "Apri report Markdown"
buttons provide direct access to the generated outputs.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the installed application version without starting the graphical
application.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/gdlex-ocr/venv
Per-user Python virtual environment.
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/gdlex-ocr/setup.log
Log of virtual environment creation and dependency installation.
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/gdlex-ocr/setup.lock
Lock directory used to serialize concurrent setup attempts.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/gdlex-ocr
Installed application sources and assets.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/gdlex-ocr/requirements.txt
Pinned Python runtime dependencies.
.TP
.I sentenza_analysis.md
Default local judgment-analysis output created next to the converted Markdown
when post-conversion analysis is enabled.
.TP
.I fascicolo_index.json
Default privacy-safe JSON output created by local casefile analysis.
.TP
.I fascicolo_index.md
Default privacy-safe Markdown output created by local casefile analysis.
.TP
.I fascicolo_index.csv
Default privacy-safe CSV document inventory created by local casefile analysis.
.TP
.I fascicolo_unita.csv
Default privacy-safe CSV with one row per PDP/TIAP documentary unit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B gdlex-ocr \-\-doctor
returns 0 when all checks pass, 1 for missing essential components, and 2
when only optional OCR support is incomplete.
.B gdlex-ocr \-\-version
returns 0 when the installed version file can be read.
Setup or application startup failures return a non-zero status.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ocrmypdf (1),
.BR tesseract (1)
